r=#ffffff>(3/22/02 1:50:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Maybe I wasn't quite clear</span><hr size=1> Melees (and everyone for that matter) can get resist gear.  My attacks as a wizard are checked against resists.  Melee attacks are checked against (from what I know) AC, evade skills/attributes.<br>
<br>
OK.  So what I was trying to say was the gear available to cut my damage SUBSTANTIALY is available to everyone.  What gear is available to casters that cuts melee damage so substantialy?<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
<br>
I was in my low 20's wandering through EC on my way to Neriak.  There's a lvl 15 druid (a DRIUD for God's sake!) pk'ing some young darks.  So I take it upon myself to make her go away.  I'm buffed up with skins/shields appropriate for my level.  I don't bother with a SoW.  I used to fight in this zone a lot, so I figure I know where she's medding.  Sure enough, I hit her with a spam of Temperate Flux staff to check her mr and get her other resists down a touch.  By the time she stands up my first nuke is on her.<br>
<br>
She was willing to just stand there and cast so I start in on her with SoL and she can't get squat off.  Every so often I'm dropping a big nuke.  Her health is hardly moving.  (A DRIUD for God's sake!)  I get her to half life, and I'm about a bubble down, but my mana is so low that all I have left is room to gate.<br>
<br>
After some tells I learn that she has resists of at least 120 is ALL categories.  Whether that was true or not, she should have been charred hippie long before I reached 40mana.  She said I was the only caster who she hasn't killed and who actually managed to hurt her.  Woopy.  What a complement from someone 5 levels lower.  (A DRUID for God's sake!)<br>
<br>
So, Aerimus, I figured my damage was being cut by about 80%.  If this was a warrior with such resists, what could I have done but gated earlier?  Lures do not apply, I'm too low of a level.  Even if they did, check the casting time.<br>
<br>
As I said, if someone doesn't have huge resist gear, chances are they're going to die.  That's why I have no problem with the damage nerf.  But I ask again:<br>
<br>
Where are the items/gear that will resist warrior damage?  Why can't I get a Dodge skill +200 ring?  How about a riposte spell?  Oh wait... that would get resisted.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ullyapakadeabn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llyap aka Deabn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/22/02 3:00:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The resist gear at lower levels</span><hr size=1> The two main differences between ac gear and resist gear for these pvp encounters are:<br>
<br>
1. Resist gear is more effective, possibly excepting pre 15<br>
<br>
2. AC gear only drops dps, resist gear drops total doable damage.<br>
<br>
Perhaps resisted spells in pvp at pre lure levels should only use mana for the damage done. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uchifiir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chifiir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/22/02 4:46:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=61>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> AC vs Resists</span><hr size=1> Resists are finite, level 1-60 items that never decrease in effectiveness.<br>
<br>
A level 60 can get a full resist against a level 2.<br>
<br>
Melee ATK scales up so quickly the AC is 95% useless.<br>
<br>
Lures (at 4.5 seconds of standing still come hit metime) are impractical for about 80% of the battles.  However, they're the only things that land for squat.  Did we mention the horrible mana-efficiency on Lures?<br>
<br>
Skin drops in 1 round, bash is on me, round two comes in.<br>
Now I'm skinless, standing there with a tank on me.  List my options, please.  Channel a nuke?  hahaha!  Even if I did it wouldn't matter, since he's got a ton of hps.  My 1-1.5k hps will drop so fast it won't even be funny.  Gate and pray for it to channel.  Anything else and you're dead (unless you're super luck in a good ss/yonder spot.)<br>
<br>
2 fast 1hs weapons, weapon procs, bash...yeah, channel it.  Go for it.<br>
<br>
So they can resist virtually all of my damage while I can resist almost none of theirs?<br>
<br>
Yay balance!<br>
<br>
